paragraphs.title: Download Advertising data set
paragraphs.text:
%sh
cd /Volumes/ramdisk
mkdir LinearRegression
cd LinearRegression
wget http://www-bcf.usc.edu/~gareth/ISL/Advertising.csv

paragraphs.title: Read the input data
paragraphs.text:
%flink
import org.apache.flink.ml.common.LabeledVector
import org.apache.flink.ml.math.DenseVector

val input = env.readCsvFile[(String, Double, Double, Double, Double)](filePath = "/Volumes/ramdisk/LinearRegression/Advertising.csv", ignoreFirstLine = true)

val labeledVectors = input.map{
    x => new LabeledVector(x._5, DenseVector(x._2, x._3, x._4))
}

paragraphs.title: Some Helper functions
paragraphs.text:
%pyflink
import StringIO
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def show(p):
  img = StringIO.StringIO()
  p.savefig(img, format='svg')
  img.seek(0)
  print '%html ' + img.buf
  
def scatterPlot(x, y):
    plt.figure()
    plt.scatter(x, y)

def asArray(javaArray):
    array = []
    for element in javaArray:
        array.append(element)
    return array

paragraphs.title: More Helper Function
paragraphs.text:
%flink
def extractLabelFeature(input: DataSet[LabeledVector], dimension: Int, labelID: String, featureID: String): Unit = {
    val labelFeatureDS = input.map(x => (x.label, x.vector(dimension)))
    val labelFeature = labelFeatureDS.collect()
    val (label, feature) = labelFeature.unzip

    z.put(labelID, label.toArray)
    z.put(featureID, feature.toArray)
}

%pyflink
feature = asArray(z.get("tv"))
label = asArray(z.get("label"))

scatterPlot(feature, label)
plt.ylabel("Sales")
plt.xlabel("TV")
show(plt)
plt.close()

paragraphs.title: Train SimpleLeastSquares
paragraphs.text:
%flink
import org.apache.flink.ml.regression.SimpleLeastSquaresRegression
import org.apache.flink.ml.preprocessing.StandardScaler

val ss = StandardScaler().setMean(0.0)
val sls = new SimpleLeastSquaresRegression()

val chain = ss.chainPredictor(sls)

chain.fit(trainingData)
//sls.fit(trainingData)

val weightVector = sls.weights.get.collect()(0)

val ssTrainingData = ss.transform(trainingData)

extractLabelFeature(ssTrainingData, 0, "label", "feature")

z.put("weightVector", weightVector.asInstanceOf[org.apache.flink.ml.math.DenseVector].data)

paragraphs.title: Plot Linear Regression
paragraphs.text:
%pyflink
label = asArray(z.get("label"))
feature = asArray(z.get("feature"))

scatterPlot(feature, label)
plt.ylabel("Label")
plt.xlabel("Feature")

x = [z.get("featureMin")[0], z.get("featureMax")[0]]
y = [z.get("minPredict"), z.get("maxPredict")]

plt.plot(x,y, color="red")

show(plt)

plt.close()

paragraphs.title: Polynomial Base Function
paragraphs.text:
%flink
import org.apache.flink.ml.preprocessing.PolynomialFeatures
import org.apache.flink.ml.common.ParameterMap

val degree = 2

// val ss = StandardScaler().setMean(0.0)
val pf = PolynomialFeatures().setDegree(degree)
val sls = new SimpleLeastSquaresRegression()
val parameters = ParameterMap().add(SimpleLeastSquaresRegression.Regularization, 0.0)

val chain = pf.chainPredictor(sls)
// val chain = ss.chainPredictor(polyChain)

// chain.fit(trainingData, parameters)
chain.fit(trainingData, parameters)

val weights = sls.weights.get.collect()(0)

// val scaledTrainingData = ss.transform(trainingData)

// extractLabelFeature(scaledTrainingData, 0, "label", "feature")
extractLabelFeature(trainingData, 0, "label", "feature")
z.put("polynomial", weights.asInstanceOf[org.apache.flink.ml.math.DenseVector].data)

%flink
val minValue = trainingData.map(x => x.vector.asBreeze).reduce{
        (left, right) => min(left, right)
    }.map(x => x.fromBreeze)
    
val maxValue = trainingData.map(x => x.vector.asBreeze).reduce{
    (left, right) => max(left, right)
}.map(x => x.fromBreeze)

val maxV = maxValue.collect()(0)
val minV = minValue.collect()(0)
val minPredict = chain.predict(minValue).collect()(0)
val maxPredict = chain.predict(maxValue).collect()(0)

z.put("featureMin", minV.asInstanceOf[org.apache.flink.ml.math.DenseVector].data)
z.put("minPredict", minPredict._2:java.lang.Double)
z.put("featureMax", maxV.asInstanceOf[org.apache.flink.ml.math.DenseVector].data)
z.put("maxPredict", maxPredict._2:java.lang.Double)

paragraphs.title: Plot Quadratic base Function
paragraphs.text:
%pyflink
import numpy as np

feature = asArray(z.get("feature"))
label = asArray(z.get("label"))
x = [z.get("featureMin")[0], z.get("featureMax")[0]]
quadraticWeights = asArray(z.get("polynomial"))

points = 20
xv = np.linspace(x[0], x[1], points)
tempXV = np.copy(xv)
resultValues = np.linspace(0, 0, points)
dimension = len(quadraticWeights)

for index in range(0, dimension):
    resultValues += quadraticWeights[dimension - index - 1]* tempXV
    tempXV *= tempXV

scatterPlot(feature, label)
plt.plot(xv, resultValues, color="red")
show(plt)
plt.close()

paragraphs.title: Multiple linear regression
paragraphs.text:
%flink
import org.apache.flink.ml.math._
import org.apache.flink.ml.preprocessing.StandardScaler

val ss = StandardScaler().setMean(0.0)
val mlr = SimpleLeastSquaresRegression()

val chain = ss.chainPredictor(mlr)
chain.fit(labeledVectors)

val mlrWeights = mlr.weights.get.collect()
